  "text": "R EAL-TIME interaction with the environment requires robots to adapt their motor behavior according to the perceived events. However, each sensorimotor cycle of the robot is affected by an inherent latency introduced by the processing time of sensors, transmission time of signals, and mechanical constraints [CITATION_1] - [CITATION_2] . Due to this latency, robots exhibit a discontinuous motor behavior which may compromise the accuracy and execution time of the assigned task.",
